
[1]exacerbate

   EXACERB'ATE, v.t. [L. exacerbo, to irritate; ex and acerbo, from
   acerbus, severe, bitter, harsh, sour. See Harvest.]

   1. To irritate; to exasperate; to inflame angry passions; to imbitter;
   to increase malignant qualities.

   2. To increase the violence of a disease.
